705477f-a.text:
Livingston Street, north side, between Clinton and Court Streets, showing the rear of Packer Collegiate Institute, founded in 1844.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
705477f-a.folder: Livingston Street & Clinton Street, Brooklyn, NY

703663f-b.text: 144 to 136 Clinton Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of Livingston Street, showing a row of attached houses, built by Wm. Evans about 1845. Nos. 138-136, the two houses on the right, were later torn down and the 12-story Insurance Building erected there. The later views show the remaining buildings, Nos. 144-140. On the left, on Livingston Street, is the St. Charles Borromeo Roman Catholic Church. View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection 1922 Views 2,3: P. L. Snerr  View 2: November 7, 1927 NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 3: August 5, 1934

705476f-a.text:
Livingston Street, west from Clinton Street, to Sidney Place. Also seen is No. 18-20 Sidney Place in the background. The view also shows 136-144 Clinton Street, at the N.W. corner of Livingston Street. In the background, on the right, is the steeple of St. Charles R.C. Church, at the
N.E. corner of Sidney Place and Livingston Street.
December 1925.
Brown Brothers.
